# Amendment History: github-auto-merge-no-ci-runs

## v1.1.0 — 2026-05-05

**Author:** Claude Sonnet 4.6 (via hephaestus:learn)
**Source:** Bulk auto-merge arming session across 14 HomericIntelligence repos, ~104 open PRs

### Changes

- Updated `description` frontmatter with 5 new trigger conditions (5)–(9)
- Updated `date` to 2026-05-05
- Added `history` frontmatter field pointing to this file
- Added 5 new "When to Use" bullet points:
  - gh pr list default limit 30 silently omits older PRs; use --limit 200
  - GraphQL "Pull request is in clean status" error is transient; retry immediately
  - GraphQL "Pull request is in unstable status" error — retry after a few seconds
  - Check allow_rebase_merge before arming; squash-only repos require --squash
  - Scheduled workflow failures (apply.yml) may not reflect required check status
- Added 3 new rows to "Failed Attempts" table
- Added 3 new commands to "Key Diagnostic Commands" section

---

## v1.0.0 — 2026-04-23 (initial)

**Author:** Claude Sonnet 4.6 (via hephaestus:learn)
**Source:** Diagnosis and fix of 11 CLEAN PRs stuck with armed auto-merge in AchaeanFleet

### Frontmatter snapshot

```yaml
name: github-auto-merge-no-ci-runs
description: "GitHub auto-merge stalls indefinitely on a CLEAN PR when no CI workflow ever runs on the branch. Use when: (1) PR has mergeStateStatus: CLEAN and auto-merge armed but hasn't merged after hours, (2) gh pr view --json statusCheckRollup returns empty array [], (3) docs-only, pod-spec, or non-code PRs stuck with armed auto-merge, (4) investigating why auto-merge didn't fire on a PR that looks ready."
category: ci-cd
date: 2026-04-23
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-ci
tags:
